description:
&lt;p&gt;Gloucestershire CCG, working with its partner provider organisations, is seeking to appoint two Infection Prevention and Control (IPC) Nurses to work with care home settings. This is an exciting new post which will work closely with the established IPC teams.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for registered nurses who have a keen interest and experience in infection control practices. The post holders will have an exciting opportunity to work closely with Gloucestershire Hospitals Trust Infection Prevention &amp; Control Team and the CCG Integrated Brokerage and Quality Team to provide nursing skills and expertise in IPC in Care Homes and work alongside senior colleagues to address risks and measure the impact on the delivery of care.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The roles will report to a Senior IPCN for Care Homes which as part of the small team, will monitor and support the improvement of the quality of infection prevention and control. The post holders must have good communications and organisational skills and the ability to influence others and be able to manage change.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The role will be initially for a term of 18 months on a fixed term contract basis although we would be happy to consider secondment applications.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Should you wish to discuss this further please contact Kerry.Holden2@nhs.net, Lead Nurse for Infection Prevention &amp; Associate Director of Infection Prevention &amp; Control&lt;/p&gt;
